  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I create Drupal modules?",
  "response": "Creating a Drupal module involves several steps. Here's a comprehensive guide:\n\n1. Basic Module Structure:\n```\nmy_module/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 my_module.info.yml\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 my_module.module\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 my_module.routing.yml (optional)\n```\n\n2. Create .info.yml File (my_module.info.yml):\n```yaml\nname: My Custom Module\ndescription: A description of my module\ntype: module\ncore_version_requirement: ^8 || ^9\npackage: Custom\n```\n\n3. Create .module File (my_module.module):\n```php\n<?php\n\nuse Drupal\\Core\\Entity\\EntityInterface;\n\n/**\n * Implements hook_help()\n */\nfunction my_module_help($route_name, \\Drupal\\Core\\Routing\\RouteMatchInterface $route_match) {\n  // Provide help text for your module\n}\n\n/**\n * Implements hook_theme()\n */\nfunction my_module_theme($existing, $type, $theme, $path) {\n  return [\n    'my_custom_template' => [\n      'variables' => [\n        'data' => NULL,\n      ],\n    ],\n  ];\n}\n```\n\n4. Routing (my_module.routing.yml - optional):\n```yaml\nmy_module.custom_page:\n  path: '/my-custom-page'\n  defaults:\n    _controller: '\\Drupal\\my_module\\Controller\\MyModuleController::build'\n    _title: 'My Custom Page'\n  requirements:\n    _permission: 'access content'\n```\n\n5. Create a Controller:\n```php\n<?php\n\nnamespace Drupal\\my_module\\Controller;\n\nuse Drupal\\Core\\Controller\\ControllerBase;\n\nclass MyModuleController extends ControllerBase {\n  public function build() {\n    return [\n      '#markup' => 'Hello, Drupal Module!'\n    ];\n  }\n}\n```\n\n6. Create a Service (my_module.services.yml):\n```yaml\nservices:\n  my_module.custom_service:\n    class: Drupal\\my_module\\MyCustomService\n    arguments: ['@current_user']\n```\n\n7. Implement the Service:\n```php\n<?php\n\nnamespace Drupal\\my_module;\n\nclass MyCustomService {\n  public function doSomething() {\n    // Custom logic\n  }\n}\n```\n\n8. Hooks and Alter Functions:\n```php\n/**\n * Implements hook_form_alter()\n */\nfunction my_module_form_alter(&$form, \\Drupal\\Core\\Form\\FormStateInterface $form_state, $form_id) {\n  // Modify forms\n}\n```\n\nKey Best Practices:\n- Follow Drupal Coding Standards\n- Use Dependency Injection\n- Implement proper hooks\n- Create configuration forms\n- Add permissions if needed\n\nModule Development Tips:\n1. Use Drupal Console or Drush for scaffolding\n2. Enable developer modules (Devel)\n3. Clear cache frequently\n4. Use version control\n5. Write unit tests\n\nCommon Hooks to Implement:\n- hook_help()\n- hook_theme()\n- hook_form_alter()\n- hook_menu_local_tasks_alter()\n- hook_entity_type_build()\n\nConfiguration:\n```php\n// Create configuration\n$config = \\Drupal::configFactory()->getEditable('my_module.settings');\n$config->set('key', 'value')->save();\n\n// Read configuration\n$value = \\Drupal::config('my_module.settings')->get('key');\n```\n\nDependency Injection Example:\n```php\nuse Drupal\\Core\\Database\\Connection;\n\nclass MyService {\n  protected $database;\n\n  public function __construct(Connection $database) {\n    $this->database = $database;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nInstallation:\n1. Place module in modules/custom/my_module\n2. Enable via admin interface or Drush\n3. Run database updates if needed\n\nResources:\n- Drupal.org Module Development Guide\n- Drupal Console\n- Drupal API Documentation\n\nRemember that Drupal module development requires understanding of:\n- Object-Oriented PHP\n- Drupal's plugin system\n- Dependency Injection\n- Hooks and event system",
  "temperature": 1.0,
